    <body>
        <div class="example">
            <p class="exampleHeadTextEmpty">Example</p>
            <p>You might have a rectangle object like this:</p>
            <p>
                <img src="../../Images/rotate_example1.png" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
            </p>
            <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="CaptureGuides.CaptureWhatsNewGuide" />
            <p>You can click on the rectangle and rotate it 45 degrees clockwise. It will then look like this:</p>
            <p>
                <img src="../../Images/rotate_example2.png" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
            </p>
            <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="CaptureGuides.CaptureEditingImagesGuide" />
            <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="MimicGuides.MimicMovieEnhancementGuide" />
            <p>You can also click on the rectangle and manually rotate it slightly counter clockwise from its original position. It will then look like this:</p>
            <p>
                <img src="../../Images/rotate_example3.png" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
            </p>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>